---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const updated = "February 24th 2026";
---

<BaseLayout 
brand="marysse" 
title="Privacy Policy"
description="Privacy policy of Marysse Design. Information on how personal data is collected, used and protected when browsing this website.">
  <section class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
    <p>
      This website is operated by Marysse (Maria Assunta Zangone),
      Via Lomellina 12, Milan (Italy).
      You may contact the Data Controller at
      <a href="mailto:info@maryssedesign.com">info@maryssedesign.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Types of Data Collected</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Browsing data (technical and usage information collected via analytics tools).</li>
      <li>Contact data (name, email address, and information voluntarily submitted through the contact form).</li>
      <li>Cookies and similar technologies (see Cookie Policy).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Purpose and Legal Basis</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To respond to enquiries and project requests (pre-contractual measures and/or consent).</li>
      <li>To analyse website performance and improve user experience (legitimate interest, subject to consent where required).</li>
      <li>To ensure website security and proper functioning (legitimate interest).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Processing and Third Parties</h2>
    <p>
      Form submissions are processed via Formspree Inc., which acts as a data processor.
      The website is hosted on Vercel Inc.
      Analytics services may include Google Analytics, which is activated only after user consent.
      These providers may process data outside the European Union, in accordance with applicable safeguards.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      Personal data submitted through the contact form is retained for up to 24 months,
      unless a professional collaboration is established, in which case data may be retained
      as required for contractual and legal obligations.
      Analytics data is retained according to the configuration of the analytics provider.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      This website may participate in affiliate programs (including Amazon Services LLC Associates Program).
      If a purchase is made through affiliate links, a commission may be earned at no additional cost to the user.
    </p>

    <h2>7. User Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Under the GDPR, users have the right to access, rectify, erase, restrict processing,
      request data portability, withdraw consent at any time, and lodge a complaint
      with the competent supervisory authority.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically.
      Users are encouraged to review this page to remain informed about how personal data is processed.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>